---
/**
 * rest-api/0005 · Figure 1 — "a version is not a URL — it's a forever cost" (hero).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/rest-api/lessons/0005-api-versioning-strategies.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the
 * MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size, stroke-width, marker-end, …).
 *
 * The source SVG references arrowhead markers (arw, arwR) that the source page
 * defines ONCE in a body-level <svg><defs> block shared by all four figures.
 * To keep each extracted figure self-contained and rendering byte-for-byte, the
 * markers it uses are embedded here in a local <defs> (ids + fills unchanged so
 * the url(#arw)/url(#arwR) references resolve).
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 156"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A version is not a packaging choice; its real cost is permanent support burden, forced migrations, and a combinatorial test matrix"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwR"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9a2417"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="20"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">A VERSION IS NOT A URL — IT'S A FOREVER COST</text
            >
            <rect x="8" y="42" width="144" height="56" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <text x="80" y="66" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700"
                >① "just pick /v1"</text
            >
            <text x="80" y="83" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >looks like packaging</text
            >
            <rect x="168" y="42" width="144" height="56" rx="9" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="240"
                y="66"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">② bump per change</text
            >
            <text x="240" y="83" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >client base fragments</text
            >
            <rect x="328" y="42" width="144" height="56" rx="9" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="400"
                y="66"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">③ forced migrations</text
            >
            <text x="400" y="83" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >on every integrator</text
            >
            <rect x="488" y="42" width="144" height="56" rx="9" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="560"
                y="66"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">④ N×N test matrix 💥</text
            >
            <text x="560" y="83" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >5 surfaces, forever</text
            >
            <line x1="152" y1="70" x2="168" y2="70" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <line x1="312" y1="70" x2="328" y2="70" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
            <line x1="472" y1="70" x2="488" y2="70" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
            <text x="320" y="128" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#7a1f12"
                >The cost of a version isn't the URL — it's the <tspan font-style="italic"
                    >permanent</tspan
                > support burden you just signed up for.</text
            >
            <text
                x="320"
                y="146"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                fill="#2f5d3a"
                font-weight="700"
                >The senior reframe: version only when a change is genuinely impossible to make
                compatibly.</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Treat versioning as packaging and you'll mint one per change, fragment clients, and maintain
        five parallel surfaces forever. <strong>The best version is often no new version.</strong>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
